text: The Nasi Padang here is very Good and the owner of the stall very kind and friendly. Their Curry Puff is very Good Crispy but not oily... Recommended
Miss my home town , this best mie soto I ever eaten. Flavourful , spicy, size just nice. Very suitable to eat when it rained this morning. Lupis also nice.

Managed by a beautiful Malay couple, they cook the most delicious muslim food in this area. It is always a dilemma for which to order, all great. Personally, I like the Mee Soto and Lontong. No one can resist their curry puffs even with a full stomach.
Mee rebus taste not bad. Have seen a lot of people ordered its lontong which the gravy looks real nice though I'm not a fan.
Try the BeehoonMee Soto, taste so so but is good service and give lots of chicken meat.
